comments.body:
 Technically speaking, this is not a regression. This issue happens when the exitOnClose property of the first/root window is set to true. Since in 3.3, exitOnClose is set to true by default (see [this commit|https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/commit/b82829e6f1471490a2866538cabffd13df80a3dc]), this issue shows even exitOnClose is not explicitly specified.
A simple test case:
{code}
var win1 = Titanium.UI.createWindow({
    backgroundColor : '#fff',
    exitOnClose: true
});
win1.open();
{code}

Here is a simple workaround until this is fixed:
{code}
var win1 = Titanium.UI.createWindow({
    backgroundColor : '#fff',
    exitOnClose: false
});
win1.addEventListener("androidback", function(){
    win1.getActivity().finish();
});
win1.open();
{code}
